table.name: blocked_shipments_parcel_label_creations
table.Comment: This table contains the information about parcel creation attempts towards shipments that were blocked, typically resulting of a failure to create it with this set of parameters. This allows to determine that the generation should instead be done manually.

table.name: matching_checks
table.Comment: A row in this table indicates an initial check has been performed to determine whether the order_line and purchase are a mismatch or not. It is either created with a mismatch_reason or a validated_matching_id, and investigated_/by are always NULL at creation. In a case of suspected mismatch, the next step will be to confirm if it really is a mismatch, investigate its cause, and if necessary ban the relevant matching key(s) in Stocks (either the supplier's, the demander's or both), and optionally take corrective actions in Operations, at which point investigated_at/by will be set. It is important to note that the investigation might reveal that the mismatch was incorrect. In that case, a validated_matching_id will be set, but the suspected_mismatch_reason will be kept for reference. The presence or absence of the validated_matching_id is therefore the only way to determine if the mismatch is real or not. Having both validated_matching_id and investigated_by NULL indicates that the mismatch is still unresolved and processing of the order line and/or purchase and all those with the same stocks_item_id will be blocked

table.name: message_template_language_versions
table.Comment: The different message template language versions for each template message. The entries are unique per (message_template_id, language_alpha2, deactivated_at) on entries that are not deactivated. For each message_template_id in the message_templates table, there must be an English version.

table.name: message_templates
table.Comment: Provides designations for message templates, and aggregates message_template_language_versions.

table.name: order_line_transmitted_tracking_info
table.Comment:
💀 Beware 💀 If you inner join to order_lines you might duplicate lines. We can have transmitted different tracking info for a single order line, for example if there's a reship after a failed delivery.
Usually, you would be interested in the last transmitted tracking info of a parcel containing the currently bound purchase.

column.name: auto_aca__never_had_tracking_after_days
column.Comment:
Full Name: auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation__never_had_tracking_after_days
If this value is set, then purchases with undecided stockly cancellation will get registered an accepted decision if it has: - never been delivered elsewhere; AND - supplier physically holds the item since > 1 day; AND - if last parcel is not the one that made supplier physically hold the item, then has no tracking info, AND - it has been cancelled for more than this value.
This handles 2 main use cases: 1. The supplier has never provided tracking information; 2. There’s a failed delivery and the supplier hasn’t provided reship tracking information.
To set this value, the supplier must have `periodic_invoicing_config_id` set. See `auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation_implies_periodic_invoicing` constraint for more information.

column.name: auto_aca__pcl_from_supplier_stuck_or_disappeared_days_after_ti
column.Comment:
Full Name: auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation__parcel_from_supplier_stuck_or_disappeared_days_after_tracking_info
If this value is set, then purchases with undecided stockly cancellation will get registered an accepted decision if it: - is cancelled for > 1 working day; AND - last parcel is from supplier; AND - last parcel status is not in {Cancelled, Delivered, Returned to Return Address}; AND - last parcel tracking information is auto tracked OR Status is Disappeared; AND - last parcel tracking info has been registered for more than this value.
This handles this use cases of lost and stuck parcels from suppliers.
To set this value, the supplier must have `periodic_invoicing_config_id` set. See `auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation_implies_periodic_invoicing` constraint for more information.

column.name: auto_aca__after_return_parcel_received_days
column.Comment:
Full Name: auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation__after_parcel_received_days
If this value is set, then purchases with undecided stockly cancellation will get registered an accepted decision if it: - is cancelled for > 1 working day; AND - was delivered elsewhere; AND - supplier physically holds the item for more than this value.
This handles this use cases returned articles to the suppliers.
To set this value, the supplier must have `periodic_invoicing_config_id` set. See `auto_assume_cancellation_acceptation_implies_periodic_invoicing` constraint for more information.

column.name: auto_return_parcel_label_asking_method
column.Comment: auto_return_parcel_label_asking_method && manual_return_parcel_label_asking_method can't be null together

column.name: auto_supplier_return_identification_label_asking_method

column.name: manual_supplier_return_labels_retrieval_method

column.name: manual_registration_submission_retailer_specific_id_regex
column.Comment: Regex to check, when manually registering a recap, that the submission RSid is syntactically correct and therefore follows the pattern of an automatic registration recap for that specific supplier.

column.name: auto_block_for_submission_price_change__rate_over_24h_threshold
column.Comment: Once the price increase changes to total volume ratio, over 24 hour, reaches the value of this field and the `suppliers.auto_block_for_submission_price_change__flat_over_24h_threshold` is reached as well, it will block distribution of all items for this supplier and invalidate all it's answers.

column.name: auto_block_for_submission_price_change__flat_over_24h_threshold
column.Comment: Once the sum of price increase changes, over 24 hour, reaches the value of this field and the `suppliers.auto_block_for_submission_price_change__rate_over_24h_threshold` is reached as well, it will block distribution of all items for this supplier and invalidate all it's answers.
